Een van de Bites gerechten ( dessert )
In verband met het grote terras ( Covid tijd ) was het restaurant zelf niet goed te fotograferen zonder andere bezoekers op de foto te zetten. Daarom deze foto van de bestek houder.

reviews.title: For the level a good and cozy restaurant.
reviews.text:
Despite the restaurant being sold to a future new owner, the food was, with due regard for the level, more than good. The Tortellini I ordered were excellent in taste and tasty. My wife had a meal salad and it was good too. It was just a pity that my wife found a 10cm hair in the food. 
Otherwise a good and cozy restaurant with nice terrace, which is located at a roundabout and along the road to a large parking lot.

reviews.title: Delicious, friendly. What do you want more?
reviews.text: I have never experienced this before: after I indicated that I have an allergy to milk protein (no lactose, slightly more complicated) I was told that the cook would make my own card so that I could eat safely. It would take a while. How fantastic! We had a great (and safe!) meal. The dogs got water and everyone was super friendly. This is certainly not where we were last. An absolute must in terms of Quality and Service! Thank you ❤️

reviews.title: Delicious
reviews.text: We had a great meal here. Nice concept of small dishes. Very tasty. Friendly staff, who gave good advice.

reviews.title: Highly recommended!
reviews.text:
Very welcoming, and delicious food!
The service was great! Smooth and welcoming helped, super friendly, certainly also to our son, who really enjoyed it.
The bites are also a must, lots of choice of delicious freshly prepared dishes!

reviews.title: setback
reviews.text:
We were very disappointed with the food in April 2024.
This is in contrast to last year. Different chef, I don't know.
A shame because we always enjoyed it very much.

reviews.title: Recommended for good and tasty food.
reviews.text: The food here is always good and tasty. Had lunch today. This time ordered from the regular menu. Was really looking forward to a good bouncer. It was delicious and the service is very friendly. The price-quality ratio is also top! They also have a nice menu with bites here. Then you choose a few small dishes and you also have a full lunch. Recommended.

reviews.title: Surprisingly all those small dishes, with the option to choose in different rounds!!
reviews.text: Delicious food, surprisingly fun! We did 5 rounds, with all nice different dishes of your own choice! Nice concept! Wines were good and friendly service! A nice carafe of water with glasses on the table without any problems! The bill on the table! With a thank you from the service, Astrid, Naomi, Robbie and Marjolein, very thoughtful!

reviews.title: Nice concept lunch bites could be executed a bit more generously.
reviews.text: Lunch bites, a nice concept with plenty of choice on the menu. Unfortunately small sandwiches, somewhat sparsely filled. That's why we weren't really full after lunch. It could be a bit more generous with, for example, more garnishes for the amount you pay.

reviews.title: Delicious food
reviews.text:
Nice concept, delicious food.
Good price/quality ratio.
Service was friendly.
Highly recommended.

reviews.title: Disappointed value for money
reviews.text: We went here for a spontaneous dinner after a trip to the sauna. The concept is very lovely with small sharing dishes, however we were extremely disappointed because of its poor value for money. Dishes were priced separately (4-5euros each) we are not amazingly big eaters and we ‘had’ to take about 10dishes;  and for example a dessert (lava cake) it was a tiny cake ; 4-5cm sprinkled with little powdered sugar.

reviews.title: Very nice lunch
reviews.text: We had a very nice lunch here. This restaurant has a great atmosphere, the staff is friendly, we really recommand Bij Ons

articleContent.title: Your go-to guide for dog-friendly travel

seoInfo.metaDescription: Traveling with your dog has never been easier—or more fun. Cities across the country boast pet-friendly hotels, parks, and activities. With CESAR® brand’s mission to make the world more pet-friendly and Tripadvisor’s top-rated spots, you can plan with confidence. Whether it’s a quick getaway or a bucket-list trip, our guides help you stay, play, and explore with your pup. Grab the leash and go!
These Black-owned spots will round out your visit, and offer a glimpse into the future of the American South.
